#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="sn7.4"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn7.4:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 7 "
msgstr "Linked Discourses 7 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn7.4:0.2"
msgid "1. Arahantavagga "
msgstr "1. The Perfected Ones "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
msgctxt "sn7.4:0.3"
msgid "4. Bilaṅgikasutta "
msgstr "4. With Bhāradvāja the Bitter "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: pts2ed1.352, sc1
msgctxt "sn7.4:1.1"
msgid "Ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā rājagahe viharati veḷuvane kalandakanivāpe. "
msgstr "At one time the Buddha was staying near Rājagaha, in the Bamboo Grove, the squirrels’ feeding ground. "

# NOTE: For bilangika, see my note on AN 3.39. Once again, this is a descriptive epithet, the comm’s explanation misses the point.
msgctxt "sn7.4:1.2"
msgid "Assosi kho bilaṅgikabhāradvājo brāhmaṇo: "
msgstr "The brahmin Bharadvāja the Bitter heard a rumor that "

msgctxt "sn7.4:1.3"
msgid "“bhāradvājagotto kira brāhmaṇo samaṇassa gotamassa santike agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajito”ti kupito anattamano yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā tuṇhībhūto ekamantaṃ aṭṭhāsi. "
msgstr "a brahmin of the Bharadvāja clan had gone forth from the lay life to homelessness in the presence of the ascetic Gotama. Angry and displeased he went to the Buddha and stood silently to one side. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn7.4:1.4"
msgid "Atha kho bhagavā bilaṅgikassa bhāradvājassa brāhmaṇassa cetasā cetoparivitakkamaññāya bilaṅgikaṃ bhāradvājaṃ brāhmaṇaṃ gāthāya ajjhabhāsi: "
msgstr "Then the Buddha, knowing what Bhāradvāja the Bitter was thinking, addressed him in verse: "

#. HTML: </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. REF: sc2
msgctxt "sn7.4:2.1"
msgid "“Yo appaduṭṭhassa narassa dussati, "
msgstr "“Whoever wrongs a man who has done no wrong, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn7.4:2.2"
msgid "Suddhassa posassa anaṅgaṇassa; "
msgstr "a pure man who has not a blemish, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn7.4:2.3"
msgid "Tameva bālaṃ pacceti pāpaṃ, "
msgstr "the evil backfires back on the fool, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn7.4:2.4"
msgid "Sukhumo rajo paṭivātaṃva khitto”ti. "
msgstr "like fine dust thrown upwind.” "

#. HTML: </p></blockquote><p>
#. REF: sc3
msgctxt "sn7.4:3.1"
msgid "Evaṃ vutte, bilaṅgikabhāradvājo brāhmaṇo bhagavantaṃ etadavoca: "
msgstr "When he said this, the brahmin Bhāradvāja the Bitter said to the Buddha, "

msgctxt "sn7.4:3.2"
msgid "“abhikkantaṃ, bho gotama … pe … "
msgstr "“Excellent, Master Gotama! …” … "

msgctxt "sn7.4:3.3"
msgid "abbhaññāsi. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "sn7.4:3.4"
msgid "Aññataro ca panāyasmā bhāradvājo arahataṃ ahosīti. "
msgstr "And Venerable Bhāradvāja became one of the perfected."

#. HTML: </p></article></section></body></html>
